**************Process Monitoring Commands******************

1. ps : It will show current shell processes.
Shell : It is a Method used to login Particular Linux Server.
There a several Shell Names but most common is binbash 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. ps -ef : Extension of ps which lists all the processes.
ps -ef is used to check all the processes that are running.
In this CMD, init is important & the first command/init process is the first process to load the RAM, load the kernel & login page etc.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. top : It is used to check the process memory, CPU consumption, process ID.
Top Command is used to monitor the live processes that are running 
PR in Top commands refers to priority, the priority depends on the task that needs to be completed first.
We can also manually change the Priority of the task as well.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. It is used to check the free memory of RAM & swap memory.
Swap Memory : It is the extra memory that will be added to the main memory after the main memory has reached to the threshold point which was set ex :80%
We will get performance and Speed issued in Swap Memory.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. du → Checking space/size of directory or files.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6. df → Check the sizes of the mounts.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7. grep → Is used to filter any word or search any word 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                              **********END**********
